infoparam.value:
MAPPING OF RX5GphyApp
Modeling the dual-core Zynq board: the upper part is the Processing System, the lower part represents the Programmable Logic.
Additional units (e.g., DMA) may be present in the Programmable Logic (PL) part. The latter contains a memory block to model the small memory banks present in the PL. This is the extreme case where one single macro IP is used to process everything. Additional external memories and Processing Units could be added.
